    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Radio Frequency suitable for all skin types?",
            "answer": "<p>Radio Frequency is suitable for most skin types and tones.</p><p>During your consultation, we assess your skin condition, medical history and treatment goals to ensure it is appropriate and safe for you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the treatment hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe the treatment as warm and comfortable.</p><p>You may feel a gentle heating sensation as the energy stimulates the deeper layers of the skin, but it is generally well tolerated.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Some clients notice a subtle tightening effect shortly after treatment.</p><p>However, the most noticeable improvements develop gradually over several weeks as collagen production increases.</p><p>Results continue improving for up to 12 weeks.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>There is minimal to no downtime.</p><p>You may experience slight redness or warmth immediately after treatment, which typically settles within a few hours.</p><p>Most clients return to normal activities the same day.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results vary depending on age, skin condition and lifestyle.</p><p>Many clients maintain results for 6–12 months, with maintenance sessions recommended to support ongoing collagen stimulation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can Radio Frequency treat the body as well as the face?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes.</p><p>Radio Frequency can be used on areas such as the face, jawline, neck, abdomen, arms and thighs to improve firmness and skin quality.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can Radio Frequency be combined with other treatments?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes.</p><p>Radio Frequency can be incorporated into a structured treatment plan and works particularly well alongside treatments such as:</p><p>• Polynucleotides</p><p>• Microneedling</p><p>• CO₂ Laser</p><p>Your clinician will advise on the safest and most effective combination for your goals.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you during your consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is radio frequency skin tightening?",
            "answer": "<p>Radio Frequency Skin Tightening uses controlled heat energy to stimulate collagen and elastin production deep within the skin, helping to firm, tighten, and smooth areas of the face and body.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is the treatment suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>It is suitable for anyone experiencing mild to moderate skin laxity, including loose skin on the jawline, cheeks, neck, stomach, or thighs.</p><p>It is ideal for clients looking for a natural, non-surgical lift.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does it hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>No, the treatment is comfortable and often described as warm and relaxing.</p><p>Most clients experience no discomfort at all.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients achieve best results with a course of 4 to 6 weekly sessions.</p><p>Maintenance treatments every 3 to 6 months help sustain long-term firmness.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results can last several months depending on age, skin condition, and lifestyle.</p><p>Because radiofrequency stimulates your skin’s natural collagen process, improvements continue to develop over time.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>There is no downtime.</p><p>You may experience mild warmth or temporary redness, but you can return to normal activities immediately.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Some clients notice immediate tightness due to collagen contraction, with deeper, longer-lasting results developing over 4 to 12 weeks as new collagen forms.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need to book a consultation before my first session?",
            "answer": "<p>No you don't your consultation is done on the day of your treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        }
